com.inqwell.any

Interface ExceptionI

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Any, Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AnyException, AnyIOException, AnyRuntimeException, BreakException, ChannelClosedException, ClassInstantiationException, ContainedException, ContinueException, DataTruncationException, DuplicateChildException, FieldNotFoundException, FlowControlException, HierarchyException, LoginException, MasqueradeException, ModelException, PermissionException, ProcessKilledException, ResourceUnavailableException, ReturnException, RuntimeContainedException, RuntimeMasqueradeException, ServiceArgumentException, SqlIOException, StackUnderflowException, TransactionException, UnexpectedCardinalityException, UnknownObjectException, UnknownServiceException, UnknownTypeException, WriteClosedChannelException

    public interface ExceptionI
extends Any
    This interface harmonises the two exception classes within Inq, AnyException and AnyRuntimeException, so they can be treated as one wherever this is required.

    This interface is only required as long as there are these two classes, given that only the latter is really required. In future, AnyException will be removed, which will also simplify Inq code exception interfaces (by removing them altogether) with corresponding code reduction. TODO.

    Version:
    $Revision: 1.4 $
    Author:
    Tom
